UML:Class.name: 8. Large company sells devices on uStore

UML:TaggedValue.value: A large company that produces devices, including such that provide help for people with disabilities, has decided to make its products easily accessible to the people who need them. So they properly describe the devices and store the information about them as a meta information of a service. Then representatives of the company assume the role of a service providers in the uStore and start offering the devices there. Once there are some purchase requests, the company cares about the arrangement of the delivery of the hardware to the end users.

UML:Class.name: 6. House keeping company sells human services on uStore

UML:TaggedValue.value:
A house keeping company desires to provide two services on uStore: 1. Cleaning service. An assisted person will order a service on a one time basis or will get a subscription for once in a period of time (e.g. week) 2. Repair service. The service will be given as a subscription - once there is a problem in a house - electricity, sewage etc., the assisted person will inform the company, a company will schedule with the assisted person a visit of a repair worker within 24 hours. There will be no additional price for every repair - only the price of the subscription.
The company uses the following marketing strategy - once a user wants to order one of the services, the other service is proposed to him with 30% reduction.

UML:Class.name: 7. Informal caregiver helps AP to find required AAL service

UML:TaggedValue.value: Informal caregiver (for example relative of AP) registers uStore and defines his role and connection to AP. uStore asks for permission from AP to add this person as his caregiver and to allow him to see/use part of his personal information. After confirmation, the caregiver can login to uStore and search based on platform and specific needs of the AP. Finally caregiver finds some appropriate service for AP and offers it to AP through uStore. AP can select to order it or to ignore the offer.

UML:Class.name: 3. Deploing company establishs all in one service and offers it to users

UML:TaggedValue.value:
A company, that specializes in deployment of AAL services, decides to create a new service - "fall detection and monitoring".
1. Hardware - a fall detection devices 2. 24/7 monitoring center - a legacy service with Web Services API 3. A software to be installed at home of the assisted person, for controlling the bracelet and communication with the 24/7 monitoring service 4.The installation service of the devices, provided by the deploying company itself
The deploying company constructs these new service from 1) Fall detection devices sold by a devices company 2) monitoring service proposed a monitoring center company 3) A software written for the deploying company by a software developer 4) the installation service of the deploying company itself. The software written for the "fall detection and monitoring" service, listens to the signals from the fall detection devices, processes the received information and once it decides that the fall is detected, it informs the 24/7 monitoring center via its Web Service API. Here the deploying company combined hardware and a legacy service, added to it specially developed software and its own installation service, and the result of this syndication is a new, more complex solution.

UML:Class.name: 1. AP registers uStore and defines home and mobile platform profiles

UML:TaggedValue.value: An assisted person has heard about the new store on the Internet specially designed to help people like her, and wants to try it. She has learned the web address and browses it via her home AAL platform. The web interface of the uStore leads her through the registration process steps, and collects information how to assist this person in a best way. The registration first gathers the most important information and continues with less important that can be skipped. The information is collected with the agreement of the assisted person. Finally, an information about the AAL platform of the assisted person is gathered, mostly automatically, so in the future the services that will be offered to the assisted person will be compatible with that platform. A person can access uStore from several platforms, and a separate profile is stored for each of them. Profiles can be edited manually, but information can be gathered automatically only if the assisted person is connected via the platform.

EAScenario.name: Basic Path
EAScenario.subject: EAID_1977BFCA_C5C7_4dc6_97D9_7FE4ABB79055

step.name: The company assumes the role of a Service Provider, and appropriatley registers as such on the uStore.

The company creates services for all of the models of devices they wish to sell. These services have detailed description of the included hardware, possibly with pictures. These services may include software, but in most cases they would not. It is important the services to be assigned to the appropriate categories.
The company uploads the services on the uStore and starts managing and selling them like any other service.
Administrator approves the services, or gives the user's account of the company a trusted status so the services are automatically approved.
The User purchases some of the services.
The System dispatches the purchase information to the company, and creates a tracker for the hardware delivery.
The company fills in and maintains the information in the tracker until the actual delivery. The information could be simply a link.

EAScenario.name: Basic Path
EAScenario.subject: EAID_1AF4979C_D430_4bc4_B8D9_8DFC2383A51C

step.name: An Assisted person searches for cleaning services
The system returns the results and among them appear the cleaning service of the Housekeeping service provider

The Assisted person reads feedback about different service providers of the cleaning services. He do not like the feedback about other service providers, so he decides to try the Housekeeping service provider
step.uses: 11.7 Supporting AAL user community 11.4 Feedback mechanism Feedback on service providers and developers

step.name: The Assisted person starts ordering the cleaning service.
The system presents him the options for ordering - one time or subscription for once in a week, once in several days etc.
The Assisted person chooses a subscription for a year once in a week cleaning
The system presents him a calendar view where he has to choose the days and times of the cleaning
The Assisted person chooses Friday, 08:00-12:00
The system proposes the Assisted person to order an additional service of the same company - the repair service for 30% reduction
The Assisted person is happy to recieve the reduction so he aggrees to subscription for a year for the repair service also

The system presents to the Assisted person an agreement that he has to sign for ordering the two services. The agreement specifies the conidtions of the cleaning and repair. For example, there will be no additional price for every repair - only the price of the subscription.
The Assisted person agrees and signs the agreement directly on the uStore
The system present to the Assisted person the price for the subscription for the both services, including the 30% reduction for the repair service
The Assisted person pays the presented price, using PayPal
The Housekeeping service provider receives a notification about the signed agreement and the order
The Housekeeping service provider receives the payment
The Housekeeping service provider starts to provide the service to the Assisted person

After a while, the Assisted person writes feedback about the service of the Housekeeping service provider. He is consent with the cleaning service, but is not happy with the repair service - the repair workers usually arrive later than schedule
step.uses: 11.4 Feedback mechanism Feedback on service providers and developers Filling feedback on service

step.name: The Housekeeping service provider is notified about the feedback.

Having read the negative feedback about the repair servce, the Housekeeping service provider addresses the Assisted Person via the chat on the uStore. The Housekeeping service provider promises to the Assisted Person to fix the problems with late arrival of the repair workers. In the meanwhile, the housekeeping service provider gives the Assisted Person a coupon for 50% reduction for subscription for additional year of repair service
step.uses: 11.2 Communication between users and service providers Communication between users and service providers

step.name: After a while, the Assisted person no longer experiences problems with the repair service - the repair workers arrive on time. The assisted person is happy with both services of the housekeeping service provider , so he writes a positive comment to the negative feedback he did prevously about the repair service of the housekeeping service provider.
step.uses: 11.4 Feedback mechanism Feedback on service providers and developers Filling feedback on service

step.name: An Assisted person searches uStore for the needed service, using words "go out switch off electrical devices"
step.uses: 4.3 Search for service Google-like search 4.4 Text based search

step.name: The system returns the results and among them appear the service "Automatic management of the environment for comfort and security". The aim of this service is to monitor the daily activity of the user in order to do two types of actions: comfort related actions and actions to improve the security of the house. The service is analyzing the information coming from the context sources and its continuously trying to discover certain situations (user goes to sleep, user cooks, user leaves home). When it detects a situation it analyzes if there is any action linked with it and executes it. The service includes: 1) sensors 2) actuators for switching on/off the devices in the house of the Assisted Person. The system knows which devices are in the house of the Assisted Person, since he uploaded his profile previously to uStore. The system uses this information to return only the services that include actuators that match the devices. 3) software for managing the sensors and actuators
step.uses: 4.5 User's context aware search Context aware 2.6 User profile Updating user profile

step.name: The Assisted person reads feedback about the service and its service provider. He likes the feedback, so he decides to order the service
step.uses: 11.7 Supporting AAL user community 11.4 Feedback mechanism Feedback on service providers and developers

step.name: The Assisted person starts ordering the service

The system presents him the contents of the service - the sensors, the actuators and the software, and an option for installation service. The contents are presented in such a way that the Assisted Person can check/uncheck the parts of the service and the total price will be changed dynamically. For example, the Assisted Person can choose which of the devices he would like to control by the service, and also the Assisted Person can choose to install everything by himself or he wants to order installation service.
step.uses: 6.2 Customizations of services Customization of services 10.2 Ordering human resources

step.name: The Assisted person chooses actuators for all the devices at his house and also orders the installation service
The system presents him a calendar view where he has to choose the days and times of the installation. The installation includes the delivery of the hardware.
The Assisted person chooses Monday, 12:00-16:00
The system present to the Assisted person the total price for the service, including the price of sensors, actuators, software and installation service
The Assisted person pays the presented price, using WebMoney

The Service delivery and maintenance provider of the Service receives a notification about the order. This Service delivery and maintenance provider is the provider of the composite AAL service of software, hardware and installation. The Service delivery and maintenance provider delegates the procurement and delivery of hardware to a Domotic device provider, it has a business contract with.
step.uses: 16.4 Notifications 12.2 Hierarchy of services 9.2 Hardware order

step.name: The Service delivery and maintenance provider receives the payment
The Service delivery and maintenance provider sends a notification and the part of the payment for the hardware to the Domotic device provider
The Domotic device provider recieves its part of payment
The Domotic device provider sends the ordered hardware to the Assisted Person
The Assisted Person follows up the delivery of hardware process via uStore

The Service delivery and maintenance provider verifies with the Assisted Person that the ordered hardware was delivered and sends a Deployer to install the service at home of the Assisted person , during the time scheduled on uStore during the order
The Deployer arrives to the Assisted Person's house on time.
The Deployer installs the hardware
The Deployer downloads and installs the software on behalf of the Assisted Person

The Assisted person fills in the realted disabilities.
The System stores the information in the session so all future content is adjusted accordingly.
The Assisted person chooses her login details (username, password) considering availability and also fills in questionaire about personal details, with e-mail address being mandatory.
The System stores the collected information and sends an e-mail with a validation link to the chosen e-mail address.
The Assisted person receives the e-mail in his mail box and clicks the validation link.

The System confirms the validation and stores the collected so far information permanently in the Assisted person 's profile. Then the user is directed to a wizard-like first-time login sequence (see next steps), which she may choose to skip as well.
The system offers the Assisted person to join existing groups, based on his profile, group popularity or any group search criteria defined by the Assisted Person
The Assisted person selects some groups and is associated with them
The System offers to the Assisted person to upload her AAL platform profile

If the Assisted Person agrees, an automatic scan is performed, and then the Assisted person is allowed to edit and confirm the result. The result also contains a property if this is a home or mobile profile.
The System stores the AAL platform profile and associates it with the Assisted Person
Finally, the Assisted person is asked whether she desires some additional roles in the system - developer, service provider or administrator.
The Assisted Person selects zero or more additional roles.
If the assisted person did select additional roles, a request e-mail is send to the administrators -s.
